The paper discusses machine learning models and optimization algorithms, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The focus on stochastic gradient descent and its convergence rates further supports these sub-categories.
